 with action on morphisms induced by functoriality of the
  pullback.

A subobject classifier in a finitely complete
category is a monomorphism
*\xhookrightarrow {\top } \Omega  such that, for every
subobject s\hookrightarrow  x, there exists a unique map x\xrightarrow {\chi _s} \Omega ,
called the characteristic or classifying map  of the subobject such
that 




