    \begin {tikzcd}
        z\ar [dr, "\exists  !", dashed]\ar [d, "d"']\ar [drr, "d", bend left] \\
        x\ar [dr, "f"'] & E\ar [r, "e"]\ar [d]\ar [dr, phantom, "\lrcorner ", very near start] & x\ar [d, "{(f, g)}"] \\
        & y\ar [r, "{(1_y, 1_y)}"'] & y\times  y\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
    \end {tikzcd}


 commute. This unique existence of such a map witnesses exactly the universal
  property of the equalizer.

